task.summary: Change project structure to work with Gradle
Make sure Gradle can find JUnit
Remove spaces field from GameBoard due to redundancy
Make class to hold main() method
Move test class to test source dir
Edit build.gradle so it can find JUnit during build
Remove test for invalid human move while build issues being sorted out
Make test class for acceptance tests

Turn GamePlayer class into interface and refactor accordingly
GamePlayer interface has default methods for move() overridden by actual Player classes. MockGamePlayer to mock out GamePlayer interface in tests. Rework setUp method in GameControlCenter to have default version and overloaded version for specifying numRows and players, removing now redundant setPlayers. GamePlayer also takes a PlayerMarker object (for future flexibility in case we ever want to use non-string markers).
Put in some placeholder code for main()
Refactor for GamePlayer interface (squash with previous commit later)
